THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 41 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. The State of Nevada, any institution of higher education
4 and any officer or employee thereof are immune from civil liability
5 for damages sustained as a result of an act or omission of the
6 State, institution, officer or employee in response to or on the basis
7 of the public-health crisis caused by the COVID-19 pandemic
8 which impacted the provision of educational services by an
9 institution of higher education during the spring semester of 2020
10 if:
11 (a) The act or omission was reasonably related to public health
12 and safety and was performed in good faith; and
13 (b) The claim arises out of or in connection with tuition or fees
14 paid to an institution of higher education for the spring semester
15 of 2020.
16  The Legislature declares that the purpose of this subsection is
17 to advance the compelling state interest in safeguarding the State
18 Treasury, ensuring the stability and long-term sustainability of
19 institutions of higher education and encouraging the State and its
20 institutions of higher education to respond effectively to future
21 health crises in alignment with federal, state and local guidance.
22 2. For the purposes of subsection 1, an act or omission of the
23 State, any institution of higher education or any officer or
24 employee thereof shall be deemed to have:
25 (a) Impacted the provision of educational services by an
26 institution of higher education during the spring semester of 2020
27 if the act or omission:
28 (1) Caused the cessation of educational services for any
29 period;
30 (2) Caused the closure of a campus or facility operated by
31 or under the control of an institution of higher education in whole
32 or in part or otherwise limited access to any such campus or
33 facility in whole or in part;
34 (3) Modified the manner in which educational services
35 were provided, including, without limitation, by authorizing or
36 requiring a transition to online or otherwise remote instruction; or
37 (4) Otherwise interfered with the provision of educational
38 services.
39 (b) Been performed in good faith if the act or omission was a
40 good faith effort to comply with any applicable:
41 (1) Federal, state or local law, regulation or ordinance; or
