1 (2) Written order, directive or other document published by
2 a federal, state or local government or regulatory body.
3 3. The immunity granted by this section is in addition to any
4 other immunity recognized by law, and all such immunities are
5 cumulative, so that the application or attempted application of any
6 one does not bar the application or attempted application of any
7 other.
8 4. As used in this section:
9 (a) “Educational services” means any offering, program or
10 benefit provided by or in connection with an institution of higher
11 education. The term includes, without limitation, educational
12 instruction, academic support services and student services,
13 regardless of whether such services are provided directly by the
14 institution of higher education or by external entities as ancillary
15 to student engagement or development.
16 (b) “Institution of higher education” means a university, state
17 college or community college which is part of the Nevada System
18 of Higher Education.
19 (c) “Student services” means any program, resource or
20 support activity provided by or in connection with an institution of
21 higher education for the purpose of enhancing the academic,
22 personal or professional development of students. The term
23 includes, without limitation, career services, health services and
24 ancillary student activities or extracurricular programs.
